05/10/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police searched the homes of five people in the village of Opae on Sunday (October 4th), as part of an investigation into an attack on border patrol agents. Officials say the search turned up weapons and ammunition. The attack occurred late Thursday, near the village of Belanovce, close to the Kosovo border. No one was injured in the incident, though the agents' vehicle was slightly damaged by gunfire. (Makfax, Sitel, A1, MIA - 04/10/09)
